title: Craft in America
description: The influence of craft making on American culture and the work of various artists are explored.

title: Lidia Celebrates America
description: A culinary celebration of the American immigrant experience.
genres: Lidia Bastianich, Laurie Donnelly, Joshua Seftel

title: Worst Cooks in America
description: Two acclaimed chefs put seemingly hopeless home cooks through a 10-day culinary boot camp in this reality competition series. At the end, the most improved cook wins $25,000.

title: How to Make It in America
description: A pair of twentysomething entrepreneurs in Brooklyn try to hustle their way to prosperity by using their street smarts and often shady connections.
genres: Ian Edelman, Stephen Levinson, Mark Wahlberg, Julian Farino, Rob Weiss, Jill Soloway, Jada Miranda, Jade Miranda

title: American Dad!
description: Cartoon antics from Seth MacFarlane ('The Family Guy') about  a gung-ho CIA agent (voice of MacFarlane), and his suburban family, which includes a hippie teen daughter. The zany supporting cast includes a randy pet goldfish who was once an East German spy and an extraterrestrial. 'Dad' debuted after the 2005 Super Bowl.

title: Ugly Americans
description: An animated comedy about humans and non-humans in New York City focuses on a social worker's attempts to help new citizens assimilate into a bizarre world where zombies, demons and assorted sci-fi creatures are the rule rather than the exception.
genres: David M. Stern, Daniel Powell, Devin Clark, Jeff Poliquin, Erik Richter

title: American Horror Story
description: A horror anthology series from Brad Falchuk and Ryan Murphy.

cast.character: Constance Langdon, Fiona, Sister Jude Martin
Misty Day, Sister Mary Eunice, Sister Mary Eunice McKee

title: The Americans
description: Two KGB spies pose as an American married couple living in 1980s Washington, D.C.

title: The Secret Life of the American Teenager
description: A drama focusing on a teenager coping with an unexpected pregnancy, followed by new motherhood.

title: America's Next Top Model
description: Aspiring models compete for a chance to break into the business in this runaway hit. Created and executive-produced by supermodel Tyra Banks, its formula of beautiful women plus unappealing behavior make it enormously popular and one of the more intriguing reality shows, with its wannabe cover girls living together in a house and, between catfights, going out on photo shoots while they vie for a modeling contract.
premiere: Tyra Banks, Ken Mok, Daniel Soiseth, Anthony Dominici, Laura Fuest

title: American Idol
description: The smash reality series showcases wannabe pop stars competing for a record deal by crooning for a panel of judges, including, most entertainingly, the acid-tongued Simon Cowell, who departed the show in 2010 after serving for nine seasons. The judges review a performer's talent (or lack thereof), and at-home viewers then vote for their favorite potential star. The show helped launch the careers of such artists as Kelly Clarkson, Carrie Underwood, Jennifer Hudson and Adam Lambert.
premiere: Simon Fuller, Nigel Lythgoe, Mona Grenier, Cecile Frot-Coutaz, Ken Warwick, Trish Kinane, Evan Prager, Jesse Ignjatovic, Per Blankens, Richard Curtis, Simon Jones, John Valasco-Mills

title: Hollywood Darlings
description: Three former child stars juggle reviving their careers as adults with being busy wives and mothers.
